OL,6,FIn legal directions to jurors before
OL,7,Ftheir deliberations, Judge Menary said
OL,8,Fthe words "grossly offensive" set a
OL,9,Fhigh threshold.
OL,11,FHe said: "You must apply the standards
OL,12,Fof an open, just and multi-racial
OL,13,Fsociety which recognises equality and
OL,14,Fdiversity and which values free
OL,15,Fexpression.
OL,17,F"'Grossly offensive' is more than
OL,18,Fmerely offensive, impolite or rude.
OL,19,FMany things said online are unpleasant
OL,20,Fand tasteless.
